RACE.RACE_TEXT: LAUREL PARK RACE 8 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 57. Maiden Claiming Purse 50840. (PLUS UP TO 15% MBF) FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES TWO YEARS OLD. Weight, 122 lbs. Claiming Price $45,000, if for $36,000, allowed 4 lbs. MD-Bred and/or MD-Sired horses may waive claiming price in this race.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: BINNIE broke a bit slow then was forced in, recovered and was taken to rate while saving ground, drafted back leaving the far turn, angled out approaching the quarter then straightened away to be five wide in upper stretch, responded to strong hand encouragement and leveled off past the three sixteenths, sustained under a firm hand ride to take command inside the sixteenth pole and drew out. HATEFUL was sent from the gate to gain a slim early advantage, sparred between rivals into and around the turn, spurted away under a drive in upper stretch, could not contain the winner with about seventy yards to go but kept on gamely to the wire. BUNNY HOP , jostled soon after the break, pulled her way forward while four wide and appearing difficult to settle, ranged up four to loom into the lane, chased on her left lead past mid stretch and came up empty in deep stretch. LADY CHARLOTTE , away last when hopping at the break, soundly bumped with BUNNY HOP, moved up outside a rival leaving the far turn and gave hard pursuit of the embattled leaders, angled four wide into the lane, altered in towards the rail for the final furlong and kept on with effort. ENEMYNUMBERNINE , urged inside while chasing, steadied briefly near the quarter pole, came out to work between runners, angled further out in the final eighth and churned on. NEXT GIRL , with the pace three deep, dueled mid turn, gave willing chase as the leader cleared past the three sixteenths, stayed on to late then faded. MEG , soundly bumped and pinched back soon after the break, was pushed along off the inside mid turn, angled four wide into the lane, shifted further out in mid stretch and offered a belated response. BLUE TRILLION , bumped after the break, edged up soon after and chased to the inside of a rival, stayed on to upper stretch then faded. KATIE'S BRAT broke inward bothering the winner, straightened and was hustled up towards the rail to engage HATEFUL, dueled to mid turn, could not keep pace under asking in upper stretch and weakened.
